\par \b Integer Division\b0 
\par 
\par This section describes functions for performing integer division. These functions are redundant when \f1 C\f0 C\f1 386\f0  is used, because in\f1  this compiler\f0  the `\f3 /\f0 ' operator always rounds towards zero. But in other C implementations, `\f3 /\f0 ' may round differently with negative arguments.\f3  div\f0  and \f3 ldiv\f0  are useful because they specify how to round the quotient: towards zero. The remainder has the same sign as the numerator. 
\par 
\par These functions are specified to return a result \i r\i0  such that the value\i  r\i0\f3 .quot*\i\f0 denominator\i0\f3  + \i\f0 r\i0\f3 .rem\f0  equals\i  numerator\i0 . 
\par 
\par To use these facilities, you should include the header file\f3  stdlib.h\f0  in your program.
\par -- Data Type: \b div_t\b0 
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This is a structure type used to hold the result returned by the \f3 div\f0  function. It has the following members:
\par 
\par \f3 int quot\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The quotient from the division. 
\par \pard\li500\f3 int rem\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The remainder from the division.
\par 
\par \pard -- Function: div_t \b div\b0  (\i int numerator, int denominator\i0 )
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This function \f3 div\f0  computes the quotient and remainder from the division of \i numerator\i0  by \i denominator\i0 , returning the result in a structure of type \f3 div_t\f0 . 
\par 
\par If the result cannot be represented (as in a division by zero), the behavior is undefined. 
\par 
\par Here is an example, albeit not a very useful one. 
\par 
\par \f3           div_t result;
\par           result = div (20, -6);
\par      
\par \f0 Now \f3 result.quot\f0  is \f3 -3\f0  and \f3 result.rem\f0  is \f3 2\f0 .
\par 
\par \pard -- Data Type: \b ldiv_t\b0 
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This is a structure type used to hold the result returned by the \f3 ldiv\f0  function. It has the following members:
\par 
\par \f3 long int quot\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The quotient from the division. 
\par \pard\li500\f3 long int rem\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The remainder from the division.
\par 
\par \pard\li500 (This is identical to \f3 div_t\f0  except that the components are of type \f3 long int\f0  rather than \f3 int\f0 .)
\par 
\par \pard -- Function: ldiv_t \b ldiv\b0  (\i long int numerator, long int denominator\i0 )
\par 
\par \pard\li500 The \f3 ldiv\f0  function is similar to \f3 div\f0 , except that the arguments are of type \f3 long int\f0  and the result is returned as a structure of type \f3 ldiv_t\f0 .
\par 
\par \pard -- Data Type: \b lldiv_t\b0 
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This is a structure type used to hold the result returned by the \f3 lldiv\f0  function. It has the following members:
\par 
\par \f3 long long int quot\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The quotient from the division. 
\par \pard\li500\f3 long long int rem\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The remainder from the division.
\par 
\par \pard\li500 (This is identical to \f3 div_t\f0  except that the components are of type \f3 long long int\f0  rather than \f3 int\f0 .)
\par 
\par \pard -- Function: lldiv_t \b lldiv\b0  (\i long long int numerator, long long int denominator\i0 )
\par 
\par \pard\li500 The \f3 lldiv\f0  function is like the \f3 div\f0  function, but the arguments are of type \f3 long long int\f0  and the result is returned as a structure of type \f3 lldiv_t\f0 . 
\par 
\par The \f3 lldiv\f0  function was added in ISO C99.
\par 
\par \pard -- Data Type: \b imaxdiv_t\b0 
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This is a structure type used to hold the result returned by the \f3 imaxdiv\f0  function. It has the following members:
\par 
\par \f3 intmax_t quot\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The quotient from the division. 
\par \pard\li500\f3 intmax_t rem\f0 
\par \pard\li1000 The remainder from the division.
\par 
\par \pard\li500 (This is identical to \f3 div_t\f0  except that the components are of type \f3 intmax_t\f0  rather than \f3 int\f0 .) 
\par 
\par See  Integers  for a description of the \f3 intmax_t\f0  type.
\par 
\par \pard -- Function: imaxdiv_t \b imaxdiv\b0  (\i intmax_t numerator, intmax_t denominator\i0 )
\par 
\par \pard\li500 The \f3 imaxdiv\f0  function is like the \f3 div\f0  function, but the arguments are of type \f3 intmax_t\f0  and the result is returned as a structure of type \f3 imaxdiv_t\f0 . 
\par 
\par See  Integers  for a description of the \f3 intmax_t\f0  type. 
\par 
\par The \f3 imaxdiv\f0  function was added in ISO C99.
