\par \pard -- Function: void \b srand\b0  (\i unsigned int seed\i0 )
\par 
\par \pard\li500 This function establishes \i seed\i0  as the seed for a new series of pseudo-random numbers. If you call \f3 rand\f0  before a seed has been established with \f3 srand\f0 , it uses the value \f3 1\f0  as a default seed. 
\par 
\par To produce a different pseudo-random series each time your program is run, do \f3 srand (time (0))\f0 .
